<item>
            <title>[BOOKKEEPER-767] Allow loopback in tests</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/BOOKKEEPER-767</link>
                <project id="12311293" key="BOOKKEEPER">Bookkeeper</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;It&apos;s not uncommon to have something like the following in /etc/hosts:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;127.0.1.1 &amp;lt;myhostname&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This breaks the bookkeeper tests because getAllowLoopback() defaults to false. We should set allow loopback to true to allow tests to run out of the box on linux machines.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
